parquet_common\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 9486, \"output\": 1194, \"cacheRead\": 14848, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 25528, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777921066968, \"responseId\": \"resp_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec2ccf0881a3b7e0f4fe8ddc9186\"}}\n[tool-exec] start id=call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d name=bash args={\"command\": \"git status --short tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common\"}\n[tool-exec] update id=call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d name=bash\n[tool-exec] update id=call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d name=bash\n   M tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/Parquet_commonTest.java\n  ?? tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/DynConstructorsInnerBuilderTest.java\n[tool-exec] end id=call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d name=bash status=success\n   M tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/Parquet_commonTest.java\n  ?? tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/DynConstructorsInnerBuilderTest.java\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \" M tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/Parquet_commonTest.java\\n?? tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/DynConstructorsInnerBuilderTest.java\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777921087258}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \" M tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/Parquet_commonTest.java\\n?? tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/DynConstructorsInnerBuilderTest.java\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777921087258}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying access modifiers**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the implications of having a package-private target class vs. public implementations in a public API. If `getConstructor` works for a package-private class, that raises questions because it usually checks if the member is public and the declaring class must be public. For methods, `getMethod` will return only public methods from public classes. So, if a class isn't public, a public method can exist, but the class itself may not be accessible.\\n\\n**Evaluating class structure**\\n\\nI'm considering whether nested public static helpers with private or public constructors in the same public test class could be idiomatic. Sure, it creates `$` in the helper class names, but that seems acceptable. However, I wonder if dynamic class loading of these classes requires additional metadata. I'm thinking nested helper classes inside tests are common, as they're fewer than top-level, but maybe a package-private class with a public constructor isn't an issue.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec2d96cc81a397d5fc4e588e5