xist, but the class itself may not be accessible.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating class structure**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether nested public static helpers with private or public constructors in the same public test class could be idiomatic. Sure, it creates `$` in the helper class names, but that seems acceptable. However, I wonder if dynamic class loading of these classes requires additional metadata. I'm thinking nested helper classes inside tests are common, as they're fewer than top-level, but maybe a package-private class with a public constructor isn't an issue.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git status --short tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 9486, \"output\": 1194, \"cacheRead\": 14848, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 25528, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777921066968, \"responseId\": \"resp_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec2ccf0881a3b7e0f4fe8ddc9186\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_dO6x8nC5mmhmDn1U6R01A5y5|fc_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec3e75fc81a3b376b651654b307d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \" M tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/Parquet_commonTest.java\\n?? tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/DynConstructorsInnerBuilderTest.java\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777921087258}]}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_start\"}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 0, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777921087262}}\n[assistant-event] thinking_start\n[thinking] **Evaluating class loader usage**\n[thinking] \n[thinking] I need to finalize my thoughts on using `new DynConstructors.Builder().impl(...)`. Since it typically defaults to `loader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()`, I'm considering if this could be an issue in a native image environment, especially regarding test classes. It seems safer to explicitly set the loader to `PublicConstructorSubject.class.getClassLoader()`. This provides clarity and avoids potential null issues. I think I'll go ahead and add that for better safety, as it won't affect dynamic loading.\n[thinking] \n[assistant-event] thinking_end\n[tool-call] start id=unknown\n[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/DynConstructorsInnerBuilderTest.java\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"        DynConstructors.Ctor<PublicConstructorSubject> constructor = new DynConstructors.Builder()\\n                .impl(PublicConstructorSubject.class.getName(), String.class, int.class)\",\"newText\":\"        DynConstructors.Ctor<PublicConstructorSubject> constructor = new DynConstructors.Builder()\\n                .loader(PublicConstructorSubject.class.getClassLoader())\\n                .impl(PublicConstructorSubject.class.getName(), String.class, int.class)\"},{\"oldText\":\"        DynConstructors.Ctor<PrivateConstructorSubject> constructor = new DynConstructors.Builder()\\n                .hiddenImpl(PrivateConstructorSubject.class.getName(), String.class)\",\"newText\":\"        DynConstructors.Ctor<PrivateConstructorSubject> c