st, but the class itself may not be accessible.\\n\\n**Evaluating class structure**\\n\\nI'm considering whether nested public static helpers with private or public constructors in the same public test class could be idiomatic. Sure, it creates `$` in the helper class names, but that seems acceptable. However, I wonder if dynamic class loading of these classes requires additional metadata. I'm thinking nested helper classes inside tests are common, as they're fewer than top-level, but maybe a package-private class with a public constructor isn't an issue.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec2d96cc81a397d5fc4e588e52d5\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-Ow-pTTn-6Z329VBSF362705OQYL5qPOUQC1FtG997vxLUZeJmgUjF41tnUtHSxdQokLR7EjH8ro5ej3UWOBu4hZC1-NAoEHxK7vco1mj2ftKs9BJPXj9CfqQKziTgHfGQJDKAjPAyN5EKTApsgdJ60_JeDSU-HHcrHBEzHDQiSDYvyLdpOclJDzozirbA6mwseOew6XaJn8xsMJh05jfO3ZPT_ZbYtcJDfFjfkcXjj5AclZUHjOCblTPkLMxgGggwZCbLITPVF9YOaVRsc6NQa-S3SYaf6mtkpwOG-fi1mDw7jvdQZocDSBy7fc_4IGO2VA5OhR02bRa-nBd1ndwVN6RDrGersbMoiwSO0puFANGkmOJYaeqCYEry9rhbxJXmO3IghOJJoasm46bhrNTCvKvB2cAky7kg_ZqqDQ2aJrT2awpg3nMQ5QDDx-Vpzaq0vM0hOfo_C7fKtWs1VSIinKrsJsdqXK4Yt7nQDFVe-xb_ugeQioNIRDKX0oqry1tGSuI5BdlW1sB74GsHyk0HmUk2PgFR2HHliH3FnwuBLq1HS9rzTt7IKiOo3vpbJqWHPe53NOyvwDiPXHWnEZv-BaTBdBoRih3IkYDJt782Fz8R7Ykhp26gmLUSffq8YSn_4bOK_f4VYz-w6kdHAWE2fdc05mtkDn9Utghf5-6MzwDpafUb2CCbYvZfEnMCGLmGeQUFXh46zsli39wo-iQAwVJTQ2GusK5AuG7-i4kWpVB1eNfxDm7-Ql_Wmwmmkv7Z-VMq_geebfUmCiEH_cK2aiIdRTSu7UNZ-tKwsJusb-YkPDe0zdDVRiy-IvSpr5mmO_jq7T1xztqSBjDO24h1NTsanuUWpFz8IYPJJn1kBD0pQyp2K1Gxay3xwHHqTTH4yNRdgXj4mQbxrnuFX5XpPe3Trzbpt5NWHOWBhpjgQA_ZGNadKU5E7QsjR84Djn0IBz9oCcEe9jDpxfY_iUwE09WWrAs0MkFGaWD7TEAHPKAzLMGOKr-9WDXtSLxTFZ2Wov7peAZLpkucdH4Izjq77C-GQUInAOAJPG1GSFXadnd-xqebFfH37NMlm_sMfi61TFoA9_PCfkgXbfs6IHSdS6RSb3k1il1A5ay9NOqVpyA3hBfYPoRrxPIymffgCHc79Uqd6FlhONxrw8BpbdohJtHXD3oOGGSTb15Gu85Kp8LjvK3phuvl4pHSHKHEFBC2owoXo2lViRPFBVljvW4GBcdI4QEO6BUnL9zoocEoMZvp_jL68